I know most artists would use a max of 6 panels a page
There's only so much stuff you can fit on one page
you have to be careful about the balance of your panels
the main point is to keep the story flowing while giving impact to the scenes
so talking scenes like this you can do 6-8 panels no problem
but action scenes sometimes need a mix of lots of panels or just a few very large panels
Or a mix of many small panels with one HUGE one
and then you gotta worry about the flow of panels
like this 6 panel is easy- left to right - down - left to right- down-
Ever have pages that are just one panel?
but if you have people trapped in a whirlpool- you might have one big panel in thhe center showing a whirlpool- and reaction shots in smaller panels slowly encircling the pool
